h Football Hall of Fame]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://scottishfootballhalloffame.co.uk/inductees-2006/ |title= Inductees 2006 |access-date=4 July 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Scotland national football team roll of honour]] : 1990 <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scotlandfootballstats.co.uk/players/sfa-hall-of-fame/ |title= SFA Hall of Fame |access-date=4 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===International appearances===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|colspan=\"3\"|[[Scotland national football team|Scotland national team]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/16379/Richard_Gough.html|title=Richard Gough|first=Benjamin|last=Strack-Zimmermann|website=www.national-football-teams.com}}</ref>\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|1983||11||1\n|-\n|1984||3||0\n|-\n|1985||6||1\n|-\n|1986||9||1\n|-\n|1987||5||0\n|-\n|1988||6||0\n|-\n|1989||4||2\n|-\n|1990||6||0\n|-\n|1991||3||1\n|-\n|1992||7||0\n|-\n|1993||1||0\n|-\n!Total||61||6\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Scotland's goal tally first.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/football_player_profile.cfm?page=2492&playerID=576&squadID=1|title=Scottish Football Association|website=www.scottishfa.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 16 June 1983 || [[Commonwealth Stadium (Edmonton)|Commonwealth Stadium]], [[Edmonton]] || {{fb|CAN}} || align=center |2\u20130 || align=center |3\u20130 || [[Friendly match|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 2. || 25 May 1985 || [[Hampden Park]], [[Glasgow]] || {{fb|ENG}} || align=center |1\u20130 || align=center |1\u20130 || [[1985 Rous Cup]]\n|-\n| 3. || 26 March 1986 || Hampden Park, Glasgow || {{fb|ROM|1965}} || align=center |2\u20130 || align=center |3\u20130 || Friendly\n|-\n| 4. || rowspan=\"2\"| 8 February 1989 || rowspan=\"2\"| [[Tsirion Stadium]], [[Limassol]] || rowspan=\"2\"| {{fb|CYP}} || align=center |2\u20132 || align=center rowspan=\"2\"